rsity of Virginia]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Gallagher wins 2013 Merrill Award|url=http://history.virginia.edu/node/2773|accessdate=28 September 2013|newspaper=Corcoran Department of History}}</ref> * 2014: [[Louise Mirrer]], president and CEO of the [[New-York Historical Society]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Philip Merrill Award|url=http://www.goacta.org/initiatives/annual_conference|publisher=American Council of Trustees and Alumni|accessdate=5 March 2015}}</ref> * 2015: [[Hank Brown]], former [[United States Republican Party|Republican]] [[politician]] and [[United States Senate|U.S. Senator]] from [[Colorado]] who served as president of the [[University of Colorado system]] from April 2005 to January 2008. * 2016: [[Niall Ferguson]] and [[Ayaan Hirsi Ali]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Ayaan Hirsi Ali and Niall Ferguson to Receive Award at Annual Higher Education Conference|url=https://www.goacta.org/news/ayaan_hirsi_ali_and_niall_ferguson_to_receive_award_at_annual_higher_educat|accessdate=2 December 2016|publisher=American Council of Trustees and Alumni|date=October 19, 2016}}</ref> * 2017: [[Robert Zimmer]], President, [[University of Chicago]] <ref>{{cite news|title=ACTA Announces Robert Zimmer as 2017 Philip Merrill Award Receipient|url=https://www.goacta.org/whatsNew/acta-announces-robert-zimmer-as-2017-philip-merrill-award-recipient|accessdate=14 August 2018|publisher=American Council of Trustees and Alumni|date=May 11, 2017}}</ref> * 2018: [[Mitch Daniels]], President, [[Purdue University]] <ref>{{cite news|title=Purdue University President to Receive ACTA’s National Award for Commitment to Academic Freedom and Affordability|url=https://www.goacta.org/news/purdue-university-president-to-receive-actas-national-award-for-commitment-to-academic-freedom-and-affordability|accessdate=14 August 2018|publisher=American Council of Trustees and Alumni|date=April 25, 2018}}</ref>
